title: 4 Rare 80s Albums [Part 56] New Wave, New Romantic
description:
Here are four more of my favorite 80's records. 

The Mockers were one of the greatest bands that ever came out of New Zealand. I have been playing their Culprit and the King album for 24 years now and it is still as enjoyable as it was then. 

FM was a Canadian band formed by Nash The Slash and his friends Cameron Hawkins and Martin Deller. Tonight album has been named as a "The Cars Record they never recorded".  

And you surely remember John Watts of the great band Fischer Z. This is his solo work.

And roaring Boys debut and only lp is a fantastic new romantic music but very hard to find these days. Please help me in seeding once yo're done.


FM - Tonight [1987]

John Watts - One More Twist [1982]

Roaring Boys - Roaring Boys [1986]

The Mockers - Culprit and the King [1985]
